The '''Ramoans''' were a [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Species/Legends|species]] whose [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] was ruined by the [[Yuuzhan Vong]]. Six years after the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], they were still being relocated to new worlds. The last stages of their relocation were supervised by [[Lowbacca]], who abandoned the project to join the side of the [[Killik/Legends|Killiks]].

At least one member of this species became a [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]]; [[Bazel Warv]] was a contemporary of [[Valin Horn|Valin]] and [[Jysella Horn]] and gave his life while protecting [[Allana Djo Solo|Allana Solo]].

==Biology and appearance==
Ramoans were larger and stronger than average [[Human/Legends|Humans]]. Their skin was jade green. They had small [[Eye/Legends|eyes]], a pig-like snout, and tusks jutting out of their mouths. They spoke in a series of grunts, oinks, and squeaks. The shape of their mouths made it very difficult to speak [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Basic]]. They may have been related to [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorreans]].

{{Species-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
[[Bazel Warv]] is the only Ramoan to have been given more than a background role. Initially, in the preview of ''[[Fate of the Jedi: Omen]]'' included with ''[[Fate of the Jedi: Outcast]]'', he was said to be a Gamorrean, and most aspects of his description could be applied to either species.

